snippet.title: Keto Salt Lake 2019 - 17 - Amber O’Hearn: Animal based nutrition beyond - fat and protein
snippet.description:
Amber O’Hearn is a data scientist by profession with a background
in math, computer science, linguistics, and psychology. She has been
studying and experimenting with ketogenic diets since 1997, and more
recently writing and speaking about her findings. Her review on the
evolutionary appropriateness and benefit of weaning babies onto a
meat-based, high fat, low carb diet, was included as testimony
defending Tim Noakes in his recent trial.  Amber has been eating a
plant-free diet since 2009.
